<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1036,1482,1545]" box="[151,281,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,272,1519,1545]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–4" captionStart-1="FIGURES 5–8" captionStart-2="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionStartId-2="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox-0="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetBox-1="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetBox-2="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId-0="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId-2="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionTargetPageId-2="4" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." captionText-2="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Figs 1–13</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1590,2013]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,681]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="105" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1590,1616]" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Description.</emphasis>
Body 
<quantity box="[370,504,1590,1617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="104" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.7 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[613,698,1591,1617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="104" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
wide (N=3). Body, except antennae and tibiae dark brown. Antennomeres I to IV brown, V to IX dark brown, X and XI yellowish. Tibiae brown. Antennal calli not separated from rest of head surface by grooves or sculpture, quadrate, punctured as vertex. Midfrontal sulcus distinct; supracallual and suprantennal sulci shallow; supraorbital sulci shallow reaching eye margin. Antenna short; antennomere I longest, almost length of antennomeres II and III together, slightly wider at apex; antennomere II rounded; antennomeres III to V longer than wide, decreasing in length; antennomere VI the smallest; antennomeres VI to X moniliform, densely pilose; antennomere XI with acute apex. Pronotum rectangular, 1.8 times wider than long. Elytra with first to third striae reaching elytral apex; fourth and fifth striae merging at medial third; sixth and seventh striae terminating at end of middle third; eighth stria reaching apex; ninth stria with deeper punctures at base becoming shallower to apex and terminating before apex (
<figureCitation box="[691,762,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[777,793,1914,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">5</figureCitation>
). Elytra with three small, rounded patches of white setae arranged as follows: one anterior between fourth and sixth striae, two medially between first and third striae and between sixth and eighth striae (
<figureCitation box="[512,578,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1958,1982]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,289,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-72@2.[151,1436,273,1935]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, paratype, male, habitus. 1, dorsal view. 2, lateral view. 3, frontolateral view. 4, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702171/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[592,608,1986,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1390,191,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[182,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species, holotype, female. 5, habitus, dorsal view. 6, habitus, lateral view. 7, habitus, frontal view. 8, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702173/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="104">5</figureCitation>
). Median lobe of aedeagus with lateral margins parallel and convergent to apex; internal sac of aedeagus with sparse pilosity and microsculpture (
<figureCitation box="[959,1077,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
). Tignum with distal area wide, rectangular, basally sclerotized, with long setae on apical margin (
<figureCitation box="[916,1002,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Vaginal palpi parallel, sides of each slightly divergent, with setae on apex; external margin on apical third slightly inflated, then oblique to rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Bursa copulatrix membranous, without sclerites, except ring with small, sclerotized plicae proximally. Spermathecal receptacle oval, less sclerotized than pump and canal; pump longer than receptacle, with apical projection elongate and curved; canal deeply curved (
<figureCitation box="[681,763,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–13" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,572,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-185@4.[151,1436,561,1933]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9–13. Brasilplatus bahianus Oliveira, Linzmeier &amp; Konstantinov, new species. 9, median lobe of aedeagus (ventral and lateral views). 10, apex of median lobe of aedeagus (lateral view). 11, spermatheca. 12, vaginal palpi. 13, tignum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5702175" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5702175/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="105">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
